    <description>ATS Basic Game two provides players with an introduction to the Advanced Tobruk System (ATS) of tactical World War II games.  ATS allows players to recreate squad level battles on maps depicting the historical areas that the battles were fought such as Arnhem, Normandy, Iwo Jima and Stalingrad.  Each hex represents 50 yards of terrain and each turn represents two minutes.  Counters represent squads, leaders, crews or individual tanks and heavy weapons.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic game II has four scenarios covering the Battle of Stalingrad in October and November 1942.  It includes a 22&amp;quot; x 34&amp;quot; map of an industrial area in Stalingrad.  The 20 page rulebook provides the core infantry and vehicle rules for the ATS system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
